We iterate over the string once to create a dictionary counting the occurrences of each digit. Then, we iterate over the string again to check if the count in the dictionary matches the actual count of each digit. Since both loops have the same number of iterations (n), the time complexity is O(n). The space complexity is also O(n) due to the dictionary. The energy consumption is low as the solution only requires a few arithmetic operations and string accesses.

